# Modern Java, not 1998 Java

## Target: Java 21 (LTS)

- Old tutorials teach the 1998 dialect — we write **modern Java** throughout

## Five features you'll use constantly

- **`var`** — local type inference (Java 10)
- **Text blocks** — `"""` multi-line strings (Java 15)
- **Records** — one-line immutable data classes (Java 16)
- **Pattern matching for `switch`** — destructuring switch expressions (Java 21)
- **Virtual threads** — millions of cheap threads (Java 21)

## The tell

- A whole class for three fields with getters/setters is **old Java** — a `record` is one line
